            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1607348447542-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1607348447542-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and very roughly chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es] </span></strong>in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly (like it hot? Keep the seeds in!)</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop the <strong>ginger</strong>, then peel and roughly chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>tomatoes </strong>into wedges</p>",
